Django TinyMCE filebrowser is a simple and flexible tool for managing your files and images from tinymce editor.

Installation:

1) Add mce_filebrowser to Your Python path
2) Add "mce_filebrowser" to INSTALLED_APPS of existing django project
3) Add configuration option `file_browser_callback` to your TinyMCE init:
	tinyMCE.init({
			...
			file_browser_callback : "mce_filebrowser"
	});
	
	Or if you use djang-tinymce specify this option in your settings:
	
	TINYMCE_DEFAULT_CONFIG = {
		...
		'file_browser_callback': 'mce_filebrowser'
	}
	
4) Make css file visible from your project
5) Run python manage.py syncdb

Important notes:

1) To correctly show the filebrowser you need to install sorl.thumbnail application.
For more details visit http://thumbnail.sorl.net

2) Your tinyMCE installation must be on current path: MEDIA_URL + js/tiny_mce, 
if not please setup correct path for <script> tags in mce_filebrowser/templates/filebrowser.html
